## Expert Summary

A loose cushion cut diamond starts at [$1,891 for a GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — 41% less than a comparable round brilliant at the same grade. That's the Pillow Premium: cushion buyers pay less per carat than round buyers across all sizes, converting budget savings into larger stones or better grades.

Lab-grown loose cushion cuts reshape the economics further. A [GIA 3ct D-VVS1 Ideal lab cushion at $5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs less than a natural 1ct round D-VVS1. A [GIA 4ct D-VVS1 Ideal lab cushion at $7,412](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25222994?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) makes four carats accessible at a price once associated with one carat.

The Modified Brilliant Split — choosing between crushed-ice cushion modified and large-facet cushion brilliant — can only be resolved loose. Make that decision before the stone is set.

For natural cushion cuts: G-VS1 GIA Ideal is the value target at every carat weight. For lab: IGI D-VVS1 Ideal at 2ct and GIA D-VVS1 Ideal at 3ct+ are the price leaders. Buy loose, watch the video, confirm the L/W ratio, then set.

