## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is a loose cushion cut diamond?
A loose cushion cut diamond is a cushion-shaped diamond sold without a setting — as an individual certified stone. It comes with a GIA or IGI grading report confirming its cut, color, clarity, carat weight, fluorescence, and measurements. Buying loose gives you full visibility into the stone before committing to a setting.

### How much does a loose cushion cut diamond cost?
Natural GIA certified: from [$1,891 for a 1ct G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Lab-grown IGI certified: from [$1,422 for a 1.5ct E-VVS2 Excellent Cushion Modified](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Price scales with carat weight, color, clarity, and certification lab.

### Is a loose cushion cut diamond cheaper than a round?
Yes — significantly. A 1ct GIA round G-VS2 Excellent costs [$3,230](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090690?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); a 1ct GIA cushion modified G-VS1 Ideal costs [$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). That's a 41% saving. The cushion's lower price is a function of market demand, not stone quality.

### What is the difference between cushion modified brilliant and cushion brilliant?
Cushion modified brilliant has small, complex facets that create a crushed-ice sparkle pattern — bright, hypnotic, and modern. Cushion brilliant has larger, chunkier facets that produce fewer, bolder flashes — more like a vintage old mine cut. Both are beautiful; the difference is visible loose and in real-world light. Most certified loose cushions today are cushion modified.

### What is a loose cushion cut diamond price at 2 carats?
Natural GIA: from [$13,679 for F-VVS2 Ideal Cushion Modified](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29359194?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Lab-grown IGI: from [$2,606 for D-VVS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The 2ct lab cushion offers extraordinary grade for the price.

### What is a loose cushion cut diamond price at 3 carats?
Natural GIA: from [$32,692 for G-VVS2 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961123?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Lab-grown GIA: from [$5,962 for D-VVS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The lab 3ct GIA cushion is one of the most compelling values in the entire diamond market.

### Should I buy a loose cushion cut or a pre-set ring?
Loose is almost always better value. You see the exact stone before committing, compare it against alternatives, and control both purchases independently. A pre-set ring often adds 20–40% on the setting. The only reason to buy pre-set is convenience or if the setting design is highly specific and difficult to replicate.

### What color grade is best for a loose cushion cut diamond?
G is the sweet spot. It reads as white in any setting, costs 40–45% less than D at 1ct, and the difference is invisible to the naked eye once set. F adds minimal visual improvement. H and I are fine in yellow gold but may show warmth in platinum or white gold at 2ct+.

### What clarity is eye-clean in a loose cushion cut diamond?
VS2 is reliably eye-clean. VS1 is overkill. SI1 can be eye-clean in cushion modified brilliants specifically — the crushed-ice faceting hides inclusions better than round brilliant. Always watch the HD video for any SI1 loose cushion before buying. SI2: not recommended without expert review.

### GIA or IGI for loose cushion cut diamond?
GIA for natural diamonds — always. GIA is stricter and universally accepted. For lab-grown loose cushion diamonds, IGI Ideal is the standard certification and offers the best price-to-grade combination. A GIA-certified lab cushion exists and carries a premium; it's worth it if resale or certification provenance matters to you.

### What is an elongated loose cushion cut diamond?
An elongated cushion cut has a length-to-width ratio above 1.15 — making it visually longer and narrower than a square cushion. It reads more like an elongated oval with cushion faceting. On the hand, it makes fingers appear longer. Inventory is thinner than square cushions; search by GIA measurements (in mm) to find the exact ratio you want. See the [elongated cushion cut guide](/elongated-cushion-cut-diamond) for full ratio guidance.

### How do I buy a loose cushion cut diamond safely?
Buy from a vendor with HD video for every stone — so you can see the actual faceting pattern before purchasing. Verify the GIA or IGI certificate number independently on the lab's website. Confirm the L/W ratio from the GIA measurements. For lab-grown, confirm the growth method (CVD or HPHT) on the certificate. Check the return policy: 30 days minimum is the standard for reputable vendors.

### Can I buy a loose yellow or pink cushion cut diamond?
Yes. Loose yellow cushion cut diamonds (GIA Fancy Yellow grade) are available from around $1,549/ct for natural, with lab-grown yellow cushion at significantly lower prices. Loose pink cushion cut diamonds start from $9,488 for 1ct natural Fancy Brownish Pink, with lab pink cushion cuts from $3,045 for 5ct Fancy Vivid Pink. See our [yellow cushion cut guide](/yellow-cushion-cut-diamond) and [pink cushion cut guide](/pink-cushion-cut-diamond) for full pricing.

### What is cushion modified brilliant loose diamond?
"Cushion modified brilliant" is GIA's official cut designation for cushion diamonds with a modified faceting arrangement — the crushed-ice style. It is the most common type of cushion loose diamond in certified inventory. The alternative is "cushion brilliant," which has a simpler, chunkier faceting pattern more like vintage cuts. Both are valid; cushion modified is more widely available and more modern in appearance.
